##The Dean, the director, the academician, the painter... all those who died in the epidemic

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

West of the river

As of 12:00 on February 22,2020, the cumulative number of reported deaths from this outbreak has reached 2,348.

These lives were lost in a sudden outbreak. They have ordinary people, but also dean, directors, academicians, painters... many are the elite in all walks of life, their departure is a huge loss in their industry, how not lamentable.

Today, let us honor the memory of those who died in the epidemic and light a candle for them.

Yang Xiaobo

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yang Xiaobo (January 1963-january 27,2020) , a native of Tianmen, Hubei Province, Master of Business Administration of Ohio University, joined the Chinese Communist Party in May 1988 and joined the work force in June 1988.

He was deputy secretary of Huangshi Municipal Party Committee, Mayor of Huangshi and chairman of Changjiang Property Insurance Co. , Ltd. . He presided over the transformation of Huangshi, the third, and Fourth Tier City that has shed its dependence on resources, and was the first financial executive to die of pneumonia in six years at the helm of Cheung Kong Property & Casualty. On January 25,2020(the first day of the Lunar New Year) , Yang Xiaobo was admitted to the Hubei Provincial People's hospital after being diagnosed with new pneumonia. He died on the night of January 27.

Red Ling

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hong Ling (November 1966-february 7,2020) , Ph. D. From University of Arizona, USA. He was a professor, professor, distinguished professor at Huazhong University of Science and Technology, member of Chinese Anti-cancer Association Nanooncology Society and National Coordinator of China Rare Disease Research Alliance. The aim of this study is to investigate the molecular mechanism of UBIAD1, a gene associated with major and rare human diseases.

On February 7,2020, Hong Ling died in Union hospital at the age of 54 due to new coronavirus infection.

Lin Zhengbin

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lin Zhengbin (July 1957-february 10,2020) , a well-known transplant specialist in China, was formerly the Deputy Director of Tongji Hospital affiliated to Tongji Medical College.

Lin Zhengbin has rich clinical experience in renal transplantation and post-operative treatment, treatment of chronic allograft nephropathy and management of various complications after renal transplantation, his work "experimental and clinical research of domestic cyclosporine Sping" won the first prize of Science and technology progress of Hubei Provincial Health Department. On February 10,2020 at 11:00 am, Professor Lin Zhengbin died due to the ineffectiveness of the new pneumonia.

Liu Shouxiang

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Shouxiang (April 1958-february 13,2020) , a native of Wuhan, Hubei Province, graduated from the Fine Arts Department of Hubei Academy of Fine Arts as a normal major. He was the deputy secretary-general of the China Artists Association, hubei Institute of Fine Arts is the former head of the Department of Fine Arts Education, a professor and a Master's advisor.

His works have been exhibited in many national art exhibitions and have been collected by the National Art Museum of China, the Shanghai Art Museum, the Jiangsu Provincial Art Museum and the Shenzhen Art Museum. Works include "cattle boy" , "bridge" and so on.

On February 13,2020, Liu Shouxiang died of new pneumonia at the age of 62.

Liu Xiaoxian

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Xiaoxian (May 1933-february 13,2020) , China's famous preventive medicine educator, founder of maternal and Child Health Professional, national Labor Medal winner. Born in Guangzhou, his ancestral home is Taishan, Guangdong. He graduated in 1957 and is still teaching in the Tongji Medical College Department of Tongji Medical College. Tongji Medical College is a professor and graduate advisor at the Public Health.

On February 13,2020, he died in Tongji Hospital of Wuhan at the age of 87.

Chang Kai

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chang Kai (?-February 14,2020) , director of Hubei Film Studio and former Director of the External Communication Department of "audiovisual". He is engaged in the "audio-visual" is to promote the revitalization of the national cultural projects, mainly committed to the opera master interpretation of the classic works to be as perfect as possible in the form of video materials to protect and pass on, he has been involved in the film "my ferry" , Chu Opera "poor world parents heart" and other works shooting and production. On February 14,2020, he died in Huangpi District, Wuhan, at the age of 55.

In this epidemic, the Changkai family was wiped out.

January 25, the first day of the New Year, Chang Kai's father cough fever, breathing difficulties, sent to a number of hospitals for treatment, have no beds to receive, multiple help, or a bed hard to get, forced to go home to save themselves.

On January 27, Chang Kai's father died.

On February 2, Chang Kai's mother died.

On February 14, Chang Kai and his sister died the same day. His sister is Liu Fan, a nurse in the injection room of the Liyuan Street Community Health Service Center of Wuchang Hospital in Wuhan, Hubei Province. On February 14,2020, at 18:30, Liu fan died of new pneumonia at the age of 59.

In just 17 days, four members of Changkai's family died.

Duan Zhengcheng

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Duan Zhengcheng (June 1934-february 15,2020) was born in Zhenjiang, Jiangsu Province. In 1957 from the central China Institute of Technology (Now Huazhong University of Science and Technology) after graduation to teach, has served as assistant, lecturer, associate professor, deputy director, director of the Department of Machinery; Professor Professor, director of the Institute of Manufacturing Automation, and chief scientist of the National Engineering Research Center for the digitization of manufacturing equipment. He has long been engaged in teaching and research of mechanical manufacturing and automation, and developed the world's first full-body gamma knife, which has made outstanding contributions to Hubei's economic development and scientific and technological progress. He was elected to the Chinese Academy of Engineering in 2009. COVID-19 died of pneumonia in hospital on February 15,2020, aged 86.

Liu Zhiming

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Zhiming (1969-february 18,2020) , a native of Shiyan, Hubei Province, graduated from the School of Medicine of Wuhan University.

He is good at the diagnosis and treatment of craniocerebral trauma, intracranial tumor, cerebrovascular disease and intraspinal diseases, especially at the surgical treatment of neurosurgical diseases.

On February 18,2020, at 10:30 a.m. , Liu Zhiming died of new coronary pneumonia.

Ke Hui Bing

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ke huibing (February 1979-february 19,2020) was born in Hoang Mai, Hubei Province. He was a professor of sociology at Huazhong University of Science and Technology and chairman of the trade union. Ke Huibing, 41, died of pneumonia in the early hours of February 19.

Ke huibing is committed to China's social welfare policy research. He is the director of the National Social Science Fund Project 2, the Huazhong University of Science and Technology Independent Innovation Fund project, and the Huazhong University of Science and Technology Teaching Research Project "teaching quality engineering" , to participate in the major research projects of philosophy and social sciences of the Ministry of Education, General Projects of the National Social Science Fund, Major projects of the key research bases of humanities and social sciences of the Ministry of Education and other national, provincial and ministerial-level projects. He was a member and secretary-general of the Professional Committee of Social Development and social security of the Chinese Sociological Society, a member of the China Social Security 30-person Forum of Young Scholars Union, and a member of the Youth Committee of the Chinese Social Security Society.

The Huazhong University of Science and Technology is also one of the hardest hit areas in the epidemic, with five professors from the Huazhong University of Science and Technology Dying of new pneumonia in the past half month. They are: Hongling, Lin Zhengbin, Liu Xiaoxian, Duan Zhengcheng and Ke huibing.
